    "name": "2026 observations",
    "description": "Consolidated raw CGM data for 2026. Each day has its own annotation in the days[] array. Readings are deduplicated across source files. Times are UTC; timezoneOffsetMinutes applies at inspection time to convert to local.",
    "timezoneOffsetMinutes":60,
    "days": [
        {
            "date":"2026-04-06",
            "notes":"All times UTC. First live monitoring session — only evening onwards captured for this calendar day. Pre-monitoring context: dinner ~18g at ~18:30, evening injection ~18:00. Recording started 19:10 with BG at 4.7. Rose to 8.8 by 20:00 (dinner settling). Bedtime snack ~22:15 BST (milk + banana ~20g fast carbs + toast with peanut butter) peaked 10.3 at 23:00 BST. Insulin consumed it in 40 min. Toast eaten too late to absorb before intermediate insulin peak — demonstrates fast carbs failing against overnight intermediate insulin peak. The overnight continuation and following morning are in 2026-04-07-full-day.json."
        },
        {
            "date":"2026-04-07",
            "notes":"All times UTC. First full day with live monitoring and food diary. Overnight from 6th (via live monitoring from 19:10 on 04-06): hypo 3.9 at 01:10 BST. Three JB rescues through the night 00:00-05:00 BST — each spiked briefly then crashed. Toast 20g around 05:00 BST brought BG to 10.1 by 06:30 BST. Food diary (BST): 07:30 injection, 07:52 porridge ~15g. 12:10 3 JBs + lentil soup ~25g total. 15:00 biscuit 10g. 15:51 small orange + yoghurt ~5g. 16:30 (corrected from 17:00) 10g snack. 18:00-19:00 glass of wine. 18:30 dinner ~20g. 21:00 4 crackers + cheese + PB ~20g. 22:30 biscuit 10g + another 10g. Overnight: 3 JB rescues (~15g each at ~01:50, ~03:00, ~05:00) + toast 20g at ~05:00. Observations: morning insulin consistently overshoots meals. Afternoon is constant grazing to stay above 6.0. Crackers at 21:00 give clean calibration: 20g from 5.7 peaked 10.7 = 4.0g/mmol."
        },
        {
            "date":"2026-04-08",
            "notes":"All times UTC. Second full day. Hypo 4.3 at 06:00-06:10 BST. Dawn spike through 9.1 by 06:50 BST. Porridge breakfast ~06:52 (15g carbs est), peaked 16.9 at 09:00 BST. Morning insulin brings it down to 8.0 by 11:30 BST. Lunch spike to 13.9 at 14:20 BST, then steady descent. Pre-dinner drop to 6.8 at 17:20 BST. Dinner spike to 10.8 at 18:50 BST. Bedtime window: 7.4-9.3 BST. Overnight: gradual fall from 8.6 to hypo 4.9 at 02:10 BST, rescue carbs pushed to 10.8 by 04:00 BST, then settled 8-9 range."
        },
        {
            "date":"2026-04-09",
            "notes":"All times UTC. Third full day — Humulin M3 + dinner-as-slow-carbs strategy. Overnight from 8th: gradual fall to hypo 4.9 at 02:10 BST, rescue carbs pushed to 10.8 by 04:00 BST, settled 8-9 range. Dawn rise from 8.2 to 9.2 by 07:40 BST. Breakfast window 08:00-08:20 BST: BG 8.7-8.5. Post-breakfast spike to 16.8 at 10:40-11:00 BST. Slow descent through afternoon, 13-12 range. Pre-dinner dip to 6.9 at 18:50 BST (bug: engine double-nudged 7.4 → 6.9 same dip, she ate 15g fast sugar total, spiked to 10.9). Dinner ~20:00 BST. Evening insulin 19:00 BST. Bedtime starchy carbs: 15g porridge 21:30 + 10g toast 22:30 (staggered, slow-release). Overnight to 10th: gentle fall from 8.2 at 01:00 BST to hypo 4.9 at 03:00 BST, rescue carbs (~25g JBs+toast) spiked to 11.1 by 04:00 BST, stable 7.7-8.2 through to dawn — the cleanest overnight so far. Best outcome of any night observed."
        },
        {
            "date":"2026-04-10",
            "notes":"All times UTC. Fourth full day — first clean overnight + morning following the dinner-as-slow-carbs + bedtime starchy strategy. Dawn holds 7.4-8.1 (cleanest morning so far vs previous days hitting 4.3-4.9). Morning insulin 07:30 BST = 06:30 UTC (12u). Breakfast peak only 11.3 at 09:00 BST — much better than previous days (16.8 on 04-09). Morning insulin brings it down well. Mid-morning through lunch shows defensive grazing pattern: multiple small dips (10:30 @ 6.9, 11:40 @ 6.2, 12:50 @ 6.9, 13:10 @ 6.2) each with small snack bounces. Lunch peak 11.3 at 14:10 BST. Afternoon plateau 9.5-10.4 for 2h. Late afternoon descent from ~10 down to 5.9 at 17:50 BST (morning insulin tail + no food = slow drift). Container restart at 17:53 BST (engine lost history mid-dip). Engine fired reactive nudge at 18:10 BST reading 5.8 — recommended 5g fast sugar + 10g starchy — user acted on it, BG rose 5.8 → 10.4 peak over 30 min. Evening insulin 19:00 BST (9u). Dinner ~19:00 BST: steak + asparagus, ZERO CARBS (not intentional as strategy — she just didn't have any). Post-dinner descent from 10.4 peak: 9.1 → 8.3 → 7.8 → 7.5 → 7.1 → 6.6 → 6.9 → 6.6 → 5.1 hypo at 20:30 BST (rapid insulin tail pulling unchecked with nothing to digest). Rescue snack around 20:30-20:40 — BG recovers 5.1 → 6.1 → 7.7 by 20:50 BST. Demonstrates cleanly: injecting Humulin M3 without matching dinner carbs = guaranteed post-dinner hypo, because the soluble component has no meal to cover."
        }
    ],
